\f1\i pdfetex
\f2\i0  and 
\f1\i pdfelatex
\f2\i0 . It is also useful if the binaries for your teTeX are installed in different locations. Obviously the substituted command must still produce a pdf output file. Write the full path to the new programs in the preference dialog.\
